# GitHub personal access token — read-only, server-side only.
#
# Used by the Hono API at /api/github/stats to produce a more accurate language
# breakdown that includes private repos (OXIQA, MOTCA, Hologo-World, MoHE-HEMS,
# synetecs, etc). The token NEVER leaves the server process; the response payload
# exposes only aggregated stats — no private repo names, URLs, or descriptions.
#
# Minimum scope — fine-grained PAT (preferred):
#   Repository access: All repositories (including orgs you want reflected)
#   Permissions:
#     - Metadata:   Read-only  (required)
#     - Contents:   Read-only  (required for /repos/.../languages on private repos)
#
# Classic PAT alternative:
#   repo  (full control of private repos — broader than needed, use only if you must)
#
# Create at https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens
# Copy .env.example → .env and fill in:

GITHUB_TOKEN=
